olive oil
1 carrot
1 Brown Onion
1 beetroot
1 white turnip
½ sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 sachet Chimichurri Seasoning
1 packet chicken breast
½ packet Apricot Sauce
10 g butter
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Garlic Dip

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Slice carrot into thick rounds. Slice onion into wedges. Cut beetroot and white turnip into small chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle with garlic & herb seasoning (see ingredients), drizzle with olive oil, then season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat and spread out evenly.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes. Set aside to cool slightly.

• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• Meanwhile, combine chimichurri seasoning, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil in a medium bowl. Add chicken and turn to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add sweet chilli sauce and the butter, turning chicken to coat.
• Transfer to a plate, then spoon over any remaining glaze.

• When the roasted veggies are done, add spinach & rocket mix and a drizzle of white wine vinegar to the tray. Gently toss to combine.
• Slice chimichurri chicken.
• Divide roast veggie toss between plates. Top with chicken (plus any resting juices).
• Dollop over garlic dip to serve. Enjoy!